    "body": "### Problem\n\n`CursorColumn` uses absolute virtual column (`w_virtcol`) for comparison via `vcol_hlc(wlv) == wp->w_virtcol`. The virtual column continues counting across wrap boundaries, so on wrapped lines, only other screen lines that have a character at that **exact absolute virtcol** get the highlight — not lines at the same **screen column**.\n\nThis means CursorColumn position appears wrong or absent when the cursor is on a wrapped (second/third/etc) visual line.\n\nAdditionally, commit ca7dd33fa7 (PR #27848) added `lnum != wp->w_cursor.lnum` checks to both the main character rendering and fill area paths, blocking CursorColumn on the cursor's own physical line entirely — even on non-cursor visual lines of a wrapped line.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Open a file with long lines:  \n   ```\n   aaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaaa\n   bbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbbb\n   cccccccccccccccccccc\n   ```\n2. Make the window narrow: `set columns=40`\n3. `set cursorcolumn`\n4. Navigate with `gj` to the second visual line of the first wrapped line\n5. The cursor column highlight either doesn't appear or appears at the wrong screen position on other lines\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n`CursorColumn` should highlight the same **screen column** on all lines, regardless of wrapping.\n\n### Version\n\nv0.13.0-dev",
